race.comment: KIRKSVILLE (6) resumes. He showed ability in two runs last time in, close up in third at Bendigo on debut, tackling a stronger race at Moonee Valley next time out. He should have improved over the break and should take beating. ALIEN ANGEL (11) is a filly by Zelzal on debut for the Hayes yard. She's won a jumpout at Pakenham leading in and looks to have the ability to measure up. SILKY SETH (9) is a well bred gelding by Super Seth out of G2 winner Fabric. Wary, watch the betting. IT'S GNARLY (5) recorded an impressive trial win at Caulfield Heath over 1000m. Looks a capable type and can be competitive.
